# academic-paper-validation-and-publication — History

## v1.0.0 (2026-05-18) — Merge of 7 skills

**Changed by:** Skill-merge swarm (Phase C Wave 2, M16 / #1778)
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
Consolidated 7 academic-paper validation and publication skills into a single canonical skill
covering the full paper lifecycle: data accuracy checks, iterative review, GO/NO-GO publication
assessment, LaTeX architecture sections with TikZ, directory consolidation for arXiv, and
multi-issue epic management.

---

## Superseded from paper-readiness-epic

```yaml
name: paper-readiness-epic
description: 'Skill: paper-readiness-epic. Use when working with paper readiness epic.'
category: documentation
date: 2026-01-01
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Covered: Managing 6-issue epic (#330) for research paper preparation — priority ordering,
systematic branch workflow, implementing statistical tests (pytest.approx migration,
simulation-based power analysis, Scheirer-Ray-Hare interaction tests), pipeline integration.

Key configs: bootstrap n_resamples=10000, power_analysis n_simulations=10000, adequate_power_threshold=0.80.

---

## Superseded from paper-revision-workflow

```yaml
name: paper-revision-workflow
description: 'Systematic workflow for revising research papers: data validation, structural improvements, and tone unification'
category: documentation
date: 2026-02-01
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Covered: Multi-phase document revision — planning with line-number fix categories, parallel
data source reading, atomic edits, structural trimming (100-line Q&A sections → 13-line
conversational prose), tone unification from academic to first-person conversational.

Key lesson: Front-load verification. Read all data sources first, create verification table, then execute fixes.

