## Superseded from paper-iterative-accuracy-review

```yaml
name: paper-iterative-accuracy-review
description: 'Second-pass review after initial paper fixes: catch internal inconsistencies introduced by edits, verify statistical effect-size labels against defined thresholds, clarify ambiguous table headers, explain counter-intuitive results, and add missing pricing context'
category: documentation
date: 2026-02-22
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Covered: Post-fix second-pass review — verifying prior fixes still correct, cross-referencing
internal descriptions of partial experiments, validating effect-size labels against paper's
own Romano (2006) threshold table (no composite labels like "medium-large"), clarifying
ambiguous table column headers, adding explanatory sentences for counter-intuitive metrics,
adding cache read pricing footnote when cache% ≥ 90%.

Verified on: ProjectScylla branch 1048-haiku-analysis-paper.

