## Superseded from publication-readiness-review

```yaml
name: publication-readiness-review
description: Comprehensive 10-category GO/NO-GO assessment framework for academic paper publication readiness
category: documentation
date: 2026-02-07
version: 2.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Covered: 10-category GO/NO-GO framework — Numerical Accuracy, Internal Consistency,
Clarity, Grammar, LaTeX Formatting, Citations, Reproducibility, Figures/Tables, Scientific
Rigor, Completeness. Citation completeness check (comm between cited.txt and bibitems.txt),
reproducibility checklist, arXiv tarball verification via build.sh.

Key lesson: BibTeX only checks syntax, not semantic correctness. Manual URL verification required.

---

## Superseded from paper-consolidation-skill

```yaml
name: paper-consolidation-skill
description: Consolidate scattered LaTeX paper files into unified directory structure with publication readiness fixes
category: documentation
date: 2026-02-07
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Covered: Directory restructuring using `git mv` to preserve history, updating internal
`\graphicspath` and `\input` paths, applying batch publication fixes (arXiv `\pdfoutput=1`
directive, content corrections, terminology standardization with `replace_all=true`).

Final structure: `docs/arxiv/dryrun/{figures,tables,data,raw,archives}`. 808 files changed
(mostly renames). Output: 32 pages, ~494-505 KB PDF.

---

## Superseded from skill-adding-architecture-sections-to-latex-academic-papers

```yaml
name: skill-adding-architecture-sections-to-latex-academic-papers
description: Add architecture sections to academic LaTeX papers with TikZ diagrams, including fixing common TikZ syntax errors and managing arxiv builds
category: documentation
date: 2026-02-07
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Covered: TikZ package imports, font-command-after-`\\` brace wrapping (prevents "missing
\item" error), stacked block diagrams vs complex DAGs, long path overflow with itemize,
dual build management (paper.tex + arxiv main.tex via build_arxiv_paper.py), cross-reference
discipline (label every table/figure immediately).

TikZ style templates included in canonical skill Results section.
